bio.experienceSummary: Originally from Kansas City Missouri, I graduated high school in 2013 and left for Ohio to attend the "English Nanny and Governess School" in Chagrin Falls, Ohio. At ENGS I earned my certificates as a Certified Professional Nanny and a Certified Newborn Care Specialist. I am also trained in Standard First Aid, Poison Prevention, EpiPen, Infant Massage, AAA Driver Awareness and Automobile Safety. I truly enjoy caring for children and being around them and have been working as a Professional Nanny on and off for now 10 years. I am active, reliable, positive and creative. I also have experience in pet sitting, house sitting and have worked as a personal assistant. I am so excited to get back into childcare and I look forward to meeting new family!

description.displayText: Jadin is wonderful with kids, mine and others. She has a bright, happy disposition and the kids and I loved her!
description.originalText: Jadin is wonderful with kids, mine and others. She has a bright, happy disposition and the kids and I loved her!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I am an RN living in New Orleans. I currently work as a Transplant Coordinator as well as some days at a local surgery center and I am looking for the occasional babysitting job. My regular schedule changes weekly but I usually have at least 5 free evenings per week and can be available for some mornings or afternoons if needed. I am a proud Auntie to a 4 and 6-year-old who I am completely obsessed with plus I am the the oldest of 13 cousins. I have been caring for all of them since they were born and babysitting as a side gig for over 15 years. I also don't mind tutoring, caring for pets or helping with housekeeping. My driving record is excellent and I am BLS and ACLS certified. I look forward to meeting you and your family!

I've been caring for children for 8 years because I'm passionate about helping them grow and develop. As a patient, calm, creative, and friendly caregiver, I ensure your child will be in good hands. I have a college degree and am comfortable caring for children of all ages. I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and have experience with CPR and First Aid.

I love to play outdoor sports, board games, and puzzles with children. I'm also happy to engage them in educational games that promote learning. To keep you informed, I provide verbal updates at pickup and regular updates via text or phone call.

description.originalText: Kennedi has been an exceptional nanny for our family. She is always punctual, responsible, and incredibly caring towards our children. Kennedi’s ability to engage with the kids through fun and educational activities has been impressive, and her genuine love for them shines through in everything she does. She has truly become a valued member of our household, and we couldn’t be happier with her service. Highly recommend her to any family in need of a reliable and loving nanny!

bio.experienceSummary:
As a friendly and patient caregiver with 2+ years of experience, my passion for supporting families drives me to provide a reliable and nurturing environment for children of all ages. I believe in open and consistent communication with parents, ensuring that they receive regular updates about their child's day and any matters that arise. While respecting the parents' lead, I'm comfortable enforcing household rules to maintain a safe and structured environment.

My approach to childcare focuses on engaging activities that promote learning and fun. From outdoor adventures to board games and educational games, I strive to make each day enjoyable and enriching for the children in my care. With a college degree and First Aid Training, I'm well-equipped to handle various situations and ensure the safety and well-being of the children I care for.

description.originalText: Greg is very polite and well mannered; he it an interesting and respectable young man ; ten out of ten would recommend ❤️‍🔥

bio.experienceSummary:
Helloo, My name is Angel ! My main focus will always be ensuring your child(ren) feels comfortable, creating a safe, engaging, and fun- loving environment. I believe in having a positive and supportive relationship with both children and their families. 

My rate increases $1 for each additional child.
Very open to negotiating pay.

I'm open to providing care in my home as well. Let's chat about what works best for your family!

I am looking for a full time family near April 2025

description.originalText: Angel was absolutely amazing! She helped my daughter with learning and development so much. You would be lucky to have someone who cares as much as she does. My daughter absolutely loved her. We are so proud of her and her growth as an individual.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Grace and I am 24 years old and about to move to Atlanta! I am looking to work mostly on week days but willing to work some weekends as well! I do not technically have any experience as a caregiver, but I am the oldest of four children and have basically been babysitting my whole life! I am willing to assist with any type of housework/errands that might need to be done as well! I am good with children and an aspiring teacher. My goal is to eventually go back to school and get my Masters in Education, but right now I am in a transition period!

Hello, my name is Nandi! I taught kindergarten for 3 years, worked in a preschool, and spent 2 years teaching English in Spain. I currently work full time in higher education, but I continue to babysit because I love kids.

I have 10+ years of experience with children in the classroom, childcare, camp, and nanny setting. I've babysat children from newborn to 15 years old for date nights and 12+ hour weekend day shifts. I nannied a family for 2 years, taking care of two sets of twins (3-year-olds and newborns). I tided the house, did laundry, and completed any other tasks needed to make life easier for the parents. I now have several families I babysit for on rotation in Atlanta. 

I believe in making a lasting impression on the families I work with by being reliable, maintaining open communication, and most importantly, building a relationship with the children. I am currently available on weekends and evenings. Please feel free to contact me with any questions!
Date night, travel and special occasions sitter. I have over 8 years of experience working with newborns, toddlers and pre-teens and enjoy working with children and families.

description.originalText: Fatoumata was our afternoon babysitter for a year (only ended because my son aged out of needing a babysitter). She was professional, punctual, and caring. I felt very comfortable having her with us and would hire her again. Can highly recommend her babysitting services!

bio.experienceSummary: I'm a 31-year-old nanny with 10 years of paid experience with kids ranging from newborns to teens. I'm a graduate of Georgia State University. I am also available for date nights and weekends. I live in Atlanta, and have my own car. I have a clean driving record and consider myself a responsible driver. I am comfortable with pets, owning a dog myself. I have references as well if you are interested. I enjoy doing arts and crafts, being outdoors, games or just simply hanging out and having a fun time with kids!

Hello! I can wear various hats and adapt to different situations or jobs with ease. If you need something done, I'm the one to do it! 

I share the middle child role out of 6 children, so I've lived with kids of every age, and have been babysitting for over 10 years. I understand people well & how to help. 

I love to cook. I am great at light housekeeping. I love to read, listen and dance to music, play outside and be creative with kids. 

I love kids' imaginations and their fearlessness of life! I try to find the balance between providing boundaries and letting kids be kids. I love to go to the park, take walks or bike rides and stay as active as kids are.
